The paper deals with denoising of magnetic resonance images using a convolutional neural network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of residual learning and multi-channel strategy also suggests the possibility of it being related to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the absence of noise level parameter, which could indicate the involvement of information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
